The paper deals with optimization problems related to geometric structures in the plane, such as finding the shortest path between two points with different speeds on a highway. This suggests that the paper belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for solving the optimization problems efficiently. The problem of finding an optimal highway for a set of points can also be viewed as a discrete optimization problem (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the problem of computing an optimal pair of highways, which can be seen as a graph-theoretic problem (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves the use of computational techniques to solve the optimization problems, which falls under the sub-category of scientific computing (cs.SI).
